lings to paper informed the shape and texture of American literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticismx1783-1850. 0aAmerican literaturexHistory and criticismx19th century. 0aAmerican literaturexMale authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican literaturey1783-1850xHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aAmitié masculine dans la littérature. 0aAmitié masculinexHistoirexÉtats-Unis. 0aHommes dans la littérature. 0aLittérature américainexHistoire et critiquex1783-1850. 0aLittérature américainexHistoire et critiquex19e siècle. 0aLittérature américainexHistoire et critique. 0aMale friendship in literature. 0aMale friendshipxHistoryxUnited States. 0aMale friendshipzUnited StatesxHistory. 0aMen in literature. 0aSympathie dans la littérature. 0aSympathy in literature. 0aÉcrits d'hommes américainsxHistoire et critique. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013367740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133677423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300133677/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles